{
  "stem": "1918.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Many, many.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There were people who-- who couldn't bear their hunger and would steal from their own sister or brother, you know, to take a piece of bread because-- a tiny piece, because there was only a tiny piece and because they simply couldn't bear it.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I cannot judge them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the other hand, I have experienced incredible kindness from my sister, who is responsible for our escape.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had the kind of emotional strength that is pretty much unmatched by many people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Chica.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She actually came to the-- to the revere in the second camp where I was on the verge of death already.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I must've weighed about 40 pounds.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I know the way I looked because I looked at my sisters, and that was my mirror.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were only eyes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no body, just bones and eyes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- my sister-- I was put in the revere, which my sister would not have allowed in Auschwitz because once you were put in the revere, you condemn yourself to the crematorium because from there, you were taken to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The revere is their version of a hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The kind of hospital no one ever saw.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in-- in the second camp, there was no crematorium, so my sisters allowed me to be in the revere so that I would not have to stand in the zahlappell.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the only saving grace of being in the revere.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it also meant that you were no longer a human being.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I certainly was not.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember that I was-- I didn't have enough emotional and physical wherewithal to get up in the middle of the night and try to go out and defecate somewhere.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
